  "market_context": "Gold on the hourly chart following a daily sweep of a low with close back inside, paired with a change in state of delivery, signalling a bullish reversal. The analyst tracks hourly expansion behaviour following the higher-time-frame reversal.",
  "key_observation": "After a daily reversal, the hourly chart cycles between large ranges (expansion) and small ranges (retracement/consolidation), with each protected swing forming when price reaches a PD array and closes over the down-close candles supporting price higher.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified a daily sweep of a low followed by a close back inside the range, paired with a change in state of delivery, anticipating a reversal.",
    "Step 2: Dropped to the hourly chart to track protected swings higher, since higher-time-frame reversals set up lower-time-frame expansion.",
    "Step 3: Observed price sweep a low and close over the down-close candles, marking the first protected swing low that must hold for the trend to continue.",
    "Step 4: As price reached into a fair value gap and closed over the next down-close candles, marked a new protected swing higher.",
    "Step 5: Noted expansive bullish candles followed by shallow six-candle retracements — confirming the expansion-to-retracement cycle.",
    "Step 6: Identified a breakout signature as price closed over the prior high and formed a new opposing candle intraday after retesting the opening price.",
    "Step 7: Tracked continuation: large range → small range → large range, with each retracement respecting down-close candles.",
    "Step 8: After three days of expansion, noted that this is typically when a retracement or reversal can set up."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "In a bullish expansion following a higher-time-frame reversal, do not wait for deep discount pullbacks — instead, look for down-close candles to be closed over at a PD array to form protected swings. Expansion alternates between large and small ranges; three days of expansion often precedes a reversal.",
